The India-U.S. Delhi Declaration of Friendship reflects the strong ties between the two countries and aims to strengthen and expand their strategic partnership. The declaration emphasizes the importance of democracy, effective governance, and fundamental freedoms, as well as an open, just, sustainable, and inclusive global order. It also highlights the significance of defense ties, addressing climate change, sustainable development, economic policies that promote job creation and rising incomes, and transparent and rule-based markets. The declaration includes commitments to hold regular summits, elevate the Strategic Dialogue to a Strategic and Commercial Dialogue, establish secure hotlines between the leaders of both countries, develop joint ventures on strategic projects, enhance security and counterterrorism cooperation, and engage in regional and multilateral consultations. The declaration also emphasizes leveraging the talents and strengths of the people of both countries to enhance sustainable and inclusive development globally.